the senate voted unanimously on monday to 
condemn the apparent execution of kidnapped marine lt col william 
higgins as an outrageous act of terrorism and urged president 
bush to consider retaliation if possible 
the vote on the amendment sponsored by senate majority leader 
george mitchell of maine and senate republican leader bob dole of 
kansas was 990 sen spark matsunaga dhawaii is ill and did not 
vote 
the united states must take the lead in bringing to an end 
what has become an international scourge mitchell said 
immediately before the senate voted 
all nations must act he said if an end is to be put to 
terrorism those nations must consult coordinate and act 
fainthearted efforts and half steps only embolden 
terrorists mitchell said the united states must not shrink 
from pursuing every effort to ensure the american people are free 
from what is now the possible danger of attack when overseas 
dole who earlier had crticized israel for not informing the 
united states before seizing suspected terrorists a step that 
allegedly led to higgins reported killing made clear his mind had 
not been changed 
he said that beyond sending a message to terrorist groups and to 
nations like iran suspected of being a driving force behind them 
we also want to send a message to our friends 
the message this is a very serious matter and we believe that 
in any future efforts there should be some notification some 
coordination and maybe more responsibility assumed by our 
friends 
outside the capitol the antidefamation league of bnai brith 
said it was shocked by doles remarks because they failed to 
place the blame for col higgins murder where it truly belongs 
with iran and the hezbollah terrorists 
we must support each other directing our efforts against 
those responsible for the evil of terrorism said a statement 
from burron s levinon chairman and abraham h foxman national 
director 
