<TEXT>
lt col william r higgins a us marine held hostage in 
lebanon and facing execution said when he graduated from high 
school that his main ambition was to make his family proud 
after he was kidnapped nearly 1 years ago his uncle said 
higgins had fulfilled that goal 
he loves his country said delbert eagle of lancaster ky 
he is capable of standing up as well as an ordinary man will 
under the circumstances i dont think they could bring enough 
pressure or pain to cause him to betray his country in any way 
eagle died four months ago 
the shiite moslems holding higgins said sunday they would hang 
him unless israel released a shiite moslem clergyman kidnapped by 
israeli commandos they gave an 8 am edt deadline for sheik abdul 
karim obeid to be freed 
when he was abducted feb 17 1988 higgins 44 headed a 
75member observer group assigned to the un peacekeeping force in 
southern lebanon he was returning from talks with a moderate 
shiite moslem militia leader that reportedly touched on foreign 
hostages 
in december higgins kidnappers said they had sentenced him to 
death as a spy for israel a statement issued by the captors did 
not state an execution date for higgins a onetime aide to former 
us defense secretary caspar weinberger 
higgins born in danville ky grew up in southern jefferson 
county ky 
by the time he left for college he was well on the way to 
fulfilling the ambition he expressed in his senior yearbook for 
my family to always be proud of me 
he won appointment to west point but he chose instead to study 
at miami university of ohio on a navy rotc scholarship 
he was commissioned as a second lieutenant when he graduated in 
1967 with a business degree and later earned masters degrees from 
pepperdine university and auburn university in alabama 
higgins served in vietnam in 1968 and 1972 and later was a rifle 
company commander in okinawa japan an instructor at the staff 
noncommissioned officers academy at quantico va and a rifle 
company commander at camp lejeune nc 
higgins served in various staff positions at marine corps 
headquarters in washington and at the pentagon and graduated from 
the national war college in 1985 
he has a 17yearold daughter christine lynn with his first 
wife bonita spalding of louisville ky 
his second wife marine maj robin higgins works at the 
pentagon 
