low creeping jungle fires fed by debris 
from hurricane gilbert have charred hundreds of miles of the 
yucatan peninsula but the beaches have been spared 
we need two or three days of continual rain to put it out we 
need another hurricane but a benevolent one said jose angel 
loria the agriculture departments top official in quintana roo 
