<TEXT>
edgar kaufmann jr a department store heir and 
architectural scholar who played a crucial role in the creation of 
frank lloyd wrights fallingwater died of leukemia monday he 
was 79 
kaufmann died at new york hospitalcornell medical center 
according to victoria newhouse a fellow editor of the 
architectural history foundation of new york 
kaufmann studied with wright in 1934 he is generally credited 
with introducing wright to his father edgar a pittsburgh 
department store magnate who wanted to build a summer home on land 
he had acquired in southwestern pennsylvania 
completed in 1936 fallingwater is considered one of wrights 
greatest architectural designs its cantilever construction 
anchored in mountain rock makes the graceful stone and white 
concrete house appear to be soaring over bear run a cascading 
stream near ohiopyle in fayette county 
in a poll several years ago by the american institute of 
architects forum the house was named the greatest example of 
american architectural design 
the elder kaufmann died in 1956 leaving the house to his son 
who used it as a summer house until 1963 when he donated the house 
and 1500 surrounding acres to the western pennsylvania 
conservancy more than 120000 people visited the house last year 
according to tom schmidt director of fallingwater 
kaufmann felt fallingwater was too great a work of art just to 
be possessed by a single person schmidt said 
its the only great wright residence that came into the public 
domain with the furniture surrounding land and the art collection 
intact schmidt said 
kaufmann became a leading wright scholar as well as a curator 
at the museum of modern art in new york city and an adjunct 
professor of architectural history at columbia university he also 
was a financial supporter of and editor at the architectural 
history foundation which publishes scholarly books 
his own book fallingwater an american country house was 
published in 1986 and is now in its tenth printing 
colleagues said kaufmann insisted that the junior at the end 
of his name be written with a lowercase j 
kaufmann had no survivors and no funeral service was scheduled 
according to mrs newhouse schmidt said a memorial service would 
be held at fallingwater next week 
