<DOCNO> AP890731-0186 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
on a quantas flight back to rome ap reporter victor simpson was 
invited to dine with the pope simpson eagerly partook of the 
lobster cocktail and rack of lamb but noticed that john paul barely 
touched his appetizer and ordered only cauliflower as a main course 
the vatican advance team headed by jesuit roberto tucci checks 
out lodging security emergency medical facilities and sites for 
the pontifical mass and youth rallies 
the pope always begins his travels on alitalia then moves on 
aboard the national airline of the country he is leaving papal 
meandering beyond the major cities to remote villages and ancient 
shrines has whitened the knuckles of the vatican press on a variety 
of aircraft creaking dc8s aging turboprop fokkers a crop 
duster polish helicopter and sovietbuilt tupolevs and ilyushins 
decorated with a crucifix no doubt for the first time in their 
flight logs 
in april air frances concorde flew the pontiff at mach 2 speed 
l920 miles across the indian ocean from the island of reunion to 
lusaka zambia 
vatican baggage master stefano falez recently retired with a 
record no airline can match we never lost a bag proudly 
boasts falez who always personally looked after the pastoral 
cross it breaks down into three pieces and fits into a case like 
a cello one constant headache was what to do with the gifts given 
everywhere to the pope often they were disposed of locally to help 
the poor 
after the assassination attempt the vatican acquired for 
prepositioning around the world a fleet of mercedesbenz 
crosscountry vehicles equipped with protective plastic windows 
loudspeaker and recorder and quick acceleration in an emergency 
the mercedes used at reunion is being shipped to mauritius for the 
asian trip 
by all rights of art and ethos this pope ought to have lived in 
the l3th century the age of the great gothic cathedrals then 
color slides of his travels could glow in stainedglass glory on 
the west facade of chartres or rheims 
headhunter tribesmen paddling dugout canoes up the sepik river 
in new guinea to catch a glimpse of the number one jesus man 
bolivians in bowler hats offering cocaine tea to the pontiff as 
a stimulant for the thin air high in the andes 
on the banks of the boyne where protestant william of orange 
triumphed and oliver cromwell ordained a neverforgotten slaughter 
the pope on his knees begging the gunmen on both sides of the 
ulster border to turn away from paths of violence 
hastings kamuzu banda in homburg hat and wielding an elephant 
tail fly flick welcoming the pope to malawi with his personal 
troop of dancers whose writhing tutus were emblazoned with 
portraits of the presidentforlife 
an angry pope raising high his pastoral cross before an altar 
in managua nicaragua devoid of a crucifix or effigies of the 
saints but decorated with portraits of revolutionary heroes john 
paul giving his gold ring to the parish priest of a rio de janeiro 
favela a shantytown 
the popes tv photogenic charm and charisma lifting up babies 
strumming a guitar at a youth rally embracing a priest dying of 
aids often comes as counterpoint to a stern and uncompromising 
message of fidelity to traditional church dogma in his homilies 
40 or 50 a trip he is unbending in his opposition to divorce 
contraception homosexuality married and women priests western 
materialism and marxisttinged liberation theology 
proclaim the message and welcome or unwelcome insist on 
it he quotes st paul to gatherings of priests and bishops 
around the world who often espouse a lessrigid theology 
the message is not always welcome there have been hostile 
audiences protestant firebrand ian paisley interrupted his address 
to the european parliament to denounce him as the antichrist 
san francisco gays chanted pope go homo a poll of dutch 
catholics showed only 39 percent welcomed his visit his image 
vanished from polish tv whenever solidarity banners came into 
camera range in managua he thundered silencio into the 
microphone as propaganda loudspeakers tried to drown out his sermon 
with marxist slogans 
nicaragua is the only government that ever tampered with our 
broadcasts says vatican radios quercetti they even 
interposed the national anthem as background to our soundtrack 
at 69 john paul ii seems virtually immune to jet lag and as 
vigorous as ever if a bit more stooped and balding but both 
friends and critics are increasingly asking why he journeys on 
many say the pope travels too much the pontiff acknowledged 
in a talk to the curia then defended his trips as authentic 
pilgrimages to the sanctuary of living people of god many of 
whom could not afford to come to rome again he cited his 
namesake st paul i love to see you 
by ceaseless travel the first nonitalian pope in 450 years has 
made the church of rome less italian and more universal 
archbishop john foley the vaticans media chief summed up the 
popes global mission essentially it boils down to being clear 
on what your message is and then preaching it or selling it if you 
will to the faithful and those you hope will become the faithful 
those near john paul say he is convinced the virgin mary 
miraculously effected his recovery from gunshot wounds that would 
have been fatal to others to enable him to perform some asyet 
unknown mission 
but there is no end in sight for the world weary vatican press 
corps the word has seeped down the scala regia the staircase 
leading to the apostolic palace that john paul ii has his heart 
set on visiting cuba the soviet union and china 
chinese is a most difficult language sighs quercetti 
even for him 
</TEXT>
