good evening warner bros marshall crenshaw 
 
marshall crenshaw has spent a meandering solo career trying to 
live up to the promise of his sparkling 1982 debut hes finally 
done it on good evening largely because hes changed many of 
the elements that made him a success in the first place 
that debut was a pristine piece of poprock hearkening back to 
the days of buddy holly but the strippeddown sound eventually 
became a trap 
good evening has crenshaw significantly toughening and 
filling out his sound with the help of slide and pedal steel 
guitarists such as david lindley sonny landreth and james burton 
john mellencamp drummer kenny aronoff completes the rock n roll 
kick 
its welcome power behind a guy who rightly or wrongly had 
developed a reputation as a rock n roll wimp mostly because of 
his sweet voice and sweet songs 
crenshaw also recognizes his limitations as a writer for the 
first time hes always been able to create a couple of catchy 
tunes per record but is unable to sustain interest through a full 
album 
here he interprets songs by richard thompson john hiatt bobby 
fuller and the isley brothers he even seeks cowriting help on 
some of his own songs the welcome diversity of voices make his own 
contributions particularly she hates to go home sound that 
much better 
the clicheridden radio girl is really the only mistake on 
this 10song album the thompsonwritten valerie and good 
hearts are particularly appealing 
it took some time probably too much for crenshaw to find 
whats right for him but the rewards here are plentiful 
