us sprint said monday it will begin offering a 
braille longdistance calling card as an aid to the blind and 
visually impaired 
all numbers necessary to complete a call are embossed on the 
card in two lines of braille the company said the customer code 
number and calling instructions also are printed on the back of the 
card normally so a sighted person can assist the customer if needed 
dialing and access instructions will be sent in a braille letter 
with the card sprint spokeswoman terri dunn said the company 
expected there would be about 50000 to 60000 potential customers 
for the card 
sprint said there is no extra charge for the braille version of 
its foncard which also offers free directory assistance and free 
overthephone bill review 
to the best of our knowledge the braille foncard is the first 
credit card suited to the needs of the blind and partially 
sighted said lawrence l lake us sprint senior vice president 
product management 
the kansas city mobased company said it developed the braille 
calling card following a customer request the company solicited 
advice and suggestions from schools and organizations serving the 
blind and partially sighted 
braille is a printing system in which characters are formed by 
patterns of raised dots felt with the fingers 
