<TEXT>
more adults in the united states west germany 
japan and britain traveled during the past year than visited a 
library or attended a sporting event play or concert an american 
express survey shows 
the poll released monday shows that 69 percent of west german 
adults had traveled in the past year compared with 40 percent who 
had attended a sporting event among us adults 63 percent had 
traveled and 56 percent had been to a sports event for britain the 
percentages were 59 percent and 40 percent respectively for 
japan 57 percent and 22 percent 
the four countries have the highest spending on travel the 
poll conducted by the gallup organization for american express 
travel related services co inc surveyed more than 6500 adults 
in march of this year 
a traveler was defined as any person aged 18 or older who had 
spent at least one night away from home in paid lodging during the 
past 12 months either domestically or abroad 
of the four nations west germans do the most international 
travel and japanese the least according to the survey 
it showed that most british and west german travelers who plan 
to take a trip before the end of summer will travel abroad 
japanese and us vacationers on the other hand are more likely 
to take domestic trips 
for those japanese who do travel overseas this summer the 
united states will be the leading destination according to the 
poll it also will be a major foreign destination for west german 
and british vacationers 
for us travelers the most popular destinations were in north 
america the caribbean and hawaii the poll showed 
