<TEXT>
a projected slowing in business activity will 
result in a decline of 3 percent in steel service center shipping 
this year the steel service center institute said monday 
the institute is a trade association representing 85 percent of 
the steel service center industry steel service centers purchase 
and distribute one out of every three tons of carbon industrial 
steel products and nearly half of all stainless steel produced in 
the united states 
a 3 percent decline would bring total us shipments for the 24 
billion steel service center industry down to 228 million tons 
shipped this year compared with 235 million tons in 1988 the 
industry has had six straight record shipping years 
the service center industry attained record shipping levels in 
the first half of 1989 as shipments climbed a slight 04 percent 
ahead of last years record pace said andrew g sharkey 
institute president 
we anticipate that the third and fourth quarters will be soft 
although not recessionary most major steelconsuming markets are 
drifting down to lower but sustainable levels of activity 
</TEXT>
