<TEXT>
unocal corps secondquarter profit rose 88 
percent due largely to real estate sales higher crude oil prices 
and improved oil shale operations the oil company said monday 
net earnings were 120 million or 102 per share on revenue 
of 308 billion in the second quarter of 1988 unocal earned 64 
million or 55 cents per share on revenue of 257 billion 
the higher real estate earnings were due to 27 million in 
aftertax gains from the sale of properties in torrance calif 
and san diego county said richard j stegemeier unocals chairman 
and president 
he said that a gain from the settlement of some pension 
obligations also increased earnings 
partially offsetting the gains were higher foreign taxes and 
increased domestic production expenses stegemeier said 
for the first six months unocal earned 207 million or 177 
per share compared with sixmonth 1988 earnings of 242 million 
or 208 per share last years results included a 134 million net 
gain from the combined effects of a change in accounting principle 
for income taxes which resulted in a 456 million gain offset by 
322 million in writedowns of some assets 
revenue for the first six months of this year totaled 57 
billion up from a restated 49 billion in the same period of 1988 
